
# BMW Sales Analytics

A SQL-based analytics project exploring BMW vehicle sales across global markets, covering revenue performance, model popularity, regional trends, and fuel type breakdown.

---

## Tools Used

- SQL (SQLite)
- Power BI

---

## Dataset

- **Source:** Kaggle (included for educational and portfolio purposes)
- **Size:** ~50,000 records
- **File:** `data/bmw_analytics.csv`

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| `record_id` | Unique row identifier |
| `Model` | BMW model (e.g. 3 Series, X5, i8) |
| `Year` | Year of sale |
| `Region` | Sales region (Asia, Europe, North America, etc.) |
| `Fuel_Type` | Petrol, Diesel, or Hybrid |
| `Transmission` | Manual or Automatic |
| `Engine_Size_L` | Engine displacement in litres |
| `Mileage_KM` | Vehicle mileage in kilometres |
| `Price_USD` | Sale price in USD |
| `Sales_Volume` | Number of units sold |
| `revenue_USD` | Derived revenue (Price × Volume) |

---

## SQL Queries

All queries are in the `sql_queries/` folder.

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `01_data_cleaning.sql` | Null checks, duplicate detection, outlier identification, and creation of the cleaned analytics table |
| `02_revenue_by_model.sql` | Total revenue, units sold, avg price, and revenue share % per model; fuel type breakdown per model |
| `03_avg_price_by_region.sql` | Average price and revenue by region; price range analysis; transmission mix by market |
| `04_sales_trend_by_year.sql` | Year-over-year revenue and volume trends; YoY growth %; best-selling model per year |
| `05_analytics_view.sql` | Reusable summary view using window functions — revenue partitioned by model, region, year, and fuel type |

